file.content:
.. Set `accountId` to `«GOVERNOR_ACCOUNT_ID»`
.. Use display name: `Governor for RB Depot`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«GOVERNOR_SERVICE_ACCOUNT»` from response `.email` field
.. {rbbc_require}
service account creation successful (HTTP 200)

//axhos_step
. *Verify
{giam_service_account}
Propagation*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/get[iam.serviceAccounts.get]
to query service account using
`«GOVERNOR_SERVICE_ACCOUNT»`
.. {rbbc_poll}
with 3-5 second intervals for up to 30 seconds if service account not immediately available
.. {rbbc_require}
service account accessible before proceeding

//axhos_step
. *Grant
{gcp_project_id}
-level Permissions*:
.. {rbtoe_iam_grant_project}
to update IAM policy on
`«INPUT_DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
.. {rbbc_use}
`«GOVERNOR_SERVICE_ACCOUNT»` as principal
.. Add role: `roles/owner` (excluding billing permissions maintained by
{rbtr_payor})
// roles/cloudbuild.connectionViewer eliminated (₣Av) — CB v2 connections no longer used
.. Set policy version: 3 for conditional binding support
.. {rbbc_require}
IAM policy update successful

//axhos_step
. *Generate
{rbtgi_rbra_file}*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts.keys/create[serviceAccounts.keys.create]
to create service account key for
`«GOVERNOR_SERVICE_ACCOUNT»`
.. Set keyAlgorithm: `KEY_ALG_RSA_2048`, privateKeyType: `TYPE_GOOGLE_CREDENTIALS_FILE`
.. Retry up to `RBGC_SA_KEY_CREATE_RETRY_MAX` times on HTTP 404 with `RBGC_SA_KEY_CREATE_RETRY_DELAY_SEC` delay between attempts
.. NOTE: SA read operations (GET by email, keys.list) may succeed while keys.create POST returns 404 "does not exist" due to write-path propagation delay. Google link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/service-accounts-create[documents]: "you might need to wait 60 seconds or more before you use the service account." The 404 confirms no key was created, making retry safe. See <<rbscig_iam_grant_contracts>>.
.. {rbbc_store}
`«GOVERNOR_PRIVATE_KEY_DATA»` from response `.privateKeyData` field
.. {rbtoe_rbra_generate}
converts
`«GOVERNOR_PRIVATE_KEY_DATA»`
to
`{rbrr_governor_rbra_file}`
.. NOTE: Script outputs copy command for RBRA file installation
.. {rbbc_warn}
if
{rbrr_governor_rbra_file}
already exists (will be overwritten)
.. {rbbc_require}
RBRA file creation successful

// CB v2 Connection Viewer verification step eliminated (₣Av) — CB v2 connections no longer used

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtr_governor}
. *Display Result*:
.. {rbbc_show}
governor reset successful
.. {rbbc_show}
governor service account: `«GOVERNOR_SERVICE_ACCOUNT»`
.. {rbbc_show}
RBRA file path:
{rbrr_governor_rbra_file}

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution resets governor state.

converts `«DIRECTOR_PRIVATE_KEY_DATA»` to `«DIRECTOR_RBRA_FILE»`

//axhos_step
. *Get Depot Project Number*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/resource-manager/reference/rest/v3/projects/get[projects.get] for
{rbrr_depot_project_id}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«PROJECT_NUMBER»` from `.projectNumber` field

//axhos_step
. *Grant Project-Level Permissions*:
.. {rbtoe_iam_grant_project} for
{rbrr_depot_project_id}
.. Add `serviceAccount:«DIRECTOR_EMAIL»` with roles:
... `roles/cloudbuild.builds.editor` (submit and manage builds)
... `roles/viewer` (read project resources)
... `roles/cloudbuild.workerPoolUser` (use private pool for vouch `builds.create`)
.. Policy version: 3
.. {rbbc_require}
IAM policy update successful

//axhos_step
. *Grant
{rbtr_mason}
Impersonation*:
.. NOTE:
{rbtr_director}
submits builds that execute as
{rbtr_mason}.
This requires `serviceAccountUser` permission on
{rbtr_mason}.
.. {rbtoe_iam_grant_sa} on
{rbtr_mason}
service account
.. Add `serviceAccount:«DIRECTOR_EMAIL»` with `roles/iam.serviceAccountUser`
.. {rbbc_require}
IAM binding successful

//axhos_step
. *Grant
{rbtgi_build_bucket}
Access*:
.. {rbtoe_iam_grant_bucket} on
{rbtgi_build_bucket}
.. Add `serviceAccount:«DIRECTOR_EMAIL»` with roles:
... `roles/storage.objectCreator` (upload sources)
... `roles/storage.objectViewer` (verify uploads)
.. {rbbc_require}
bucket IAM update successful

//axhos_step
. *Grant
{rbtgi_repository}
Admin Access*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories/getIamPolicy[repositories.getIamPolicy] via HTTP GET with `options.requestedPolicyVersion=3` query parameter
.. NOTE: {gar_registry} proto specifies GET for `getIamPolicy` with no `additional_bindings` for POST. Using POST fails intermittently with HTTP 404 (transcoding layer rejection, not missing repository). See <<rbscig_iam_grant_contracts>>.
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 — 404 means repository does not exist (real error, not empty policy)
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories/setIamPolicy[repositories.setIamPolicy] for
{rbtgi_repository}
.. *Complete policy write*: Add ALL expected bindings to the read policy, regardless of what the read returned:
... `serviceAccount:«DIRECTOR_EMAIL»` with `roles/artifactregistry.repoAdmin` — Director manages images
... `serviceAccount:«MASON_EMAIL»` with `roles/artifactregistry.writer` — Mason pushes images at build time
.. NOTE: Same complete-policy-write pattern as the secret IAM step. Prevents stale read from overwriting Mason's writer binding set by {rbtgo_depot_levy}.
.. {rbbc_require}
repository IAM set with all expected bindings

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtgi_rbra_file}
. *Display Installation Instructions*:
.. {rbbc_show}
Director created successfully
.. {rbbc_show}
RBRA file location: `«DIRECTOR_RBRA_FILE»`
.. {rbbc_show}
installation command:
... `cp "«DIRECTOR_RBRA_FILE»" "{rbrr_director_rbra_file}"`

if USER_MANAGED keys found: "Manual cleanup required via Console"

//axhos_step
. *Generate Service Account Key*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts.keys/create[serviceAccounts.keys.create] for `«RETRIEVER_EMAIL»` with:
... privateKeyType: `TYPE_GOOGLE_CREDENTIALS_FILE`
.. Retry up to `RBGC_SA_KEY_CREATE_RETRY_MAX` times on HTTP 404 with `RBGC_SA_KEY_CREATE_RETRY_DELAY_SEC` delay between attempts
.. NOTE: SA read operations (GET by email, keys.list) may succeed while keys.create POST returns 404 "does not exist" due to write-path propagation delay. Google link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/service-accounts-create[documents]: "you might need to wait 60 seconds or more before you use the service account." The 404 confirms no key was created, making retry safe. See <<rbscig_iam_grant_contracts>>.
.. {rbbc_store}
`«RETRIEVER_PRIVATE_KEY_DATA»` from response `.privateKeyData` field
.. {rbtoe_rbra_generate}
converts `«RETRIEVER_PRIVATE_KEY_DATA»` to `«RETRIEVER_RBRA_FILE»`

//axhos_step
. *Grant
{rbtgi_repository}
Read Access*:
.. {rbtoe_iam_grant_project} for
{rbrr_depot_project_id}
.. Add `serviceAccount:«RETRIEVER_EMAIL»` with role:
... `roles/artifactregistry.reader` (read-only access to all Artifact Registry repositories)
.. Policy version: 3
.. {rbbc_require}
IAM policy update successful

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtgi_rbra_file}
. *Display Installation Instructions*:
.. {rbbc_show}
Retriever created successfully
.. {rbbc_show}
RBRA file location: `«RETRIEVER_RBRA_FILE»`
.. {rbbc_show}
installation command:
... `cp "«RETRIEVER_RBRA_FILE»" "{rbrr_retriever_rbra_file}"`
.. {rbbc_warn}
if
{rbrr_retriever_rbra_file}
already exists

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution charters retriever service account with read-only Artifact Registry access and provides RBRA file installation command.
